               <msContents>
                  <summary>Seed loans of wheat and barley; the entries consist of names (originally about 210 names), dates, and amounts of wheat and barley</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Written across the fibers; on the front P.Col. II 1 recto 2</note>
                     <note type="general">19 cols of writing with 257 lines in the first 17 cols.; the last cols. are in bad condition  and contain approximately 21 lines</note>
                     <note type="general">Written in a small cursive hand with enlargement of initial letters</note>
                     <note type="general">The names are in alphabetical order</note>
                     <note type="general">The document is a select, not a comprehensive register of Theadelphians</note>
                     <note type="general">Women are not included: the men whose names appear undertook the cultivation under forced leases</note>
                     <note type="general">The document was not an official report, but was drawn up to gather together various individual notations of seed loans scattered in the daybooks of the sitologoi: no areas of land and no assessment are given; there are no check marks indicating complete payment</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">In Greek</textLang>
                  </msItemStruct>
               </msContents>
